   <talk_paragraph index="n1871_trader_april-accepting-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-accepting-b" mid="11" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Mightn't that be right? You'll find out what kind of gem it is if you take it there.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="10"><![CDATA[<html>$Merchant April$<BR>There’s a lot, huh? The <FONT color=#a82424>Coral Stone</FONT>, the<FONT color=#a82424> Lapis Lazuli</FONT>, and the<FONT color=#a82424> Aquamarine</FONT>... They all kinda stir the imagination.<BR>They said one <FONT color=#086171>gem comes from the sea</FONT>, one <FONT color=#086171>gem comes from across the sea</FONT>, and one <FONT color=#086171>gem looks like the sea</FONT>, right? Are these ones you found the right ones? </html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1871_trader_april-accepting-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-accepting-acceptted" mid="13" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html><FONT color=#086171>(Accept quest)</FONT></html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="12"><![CDATA[<html>$Gem’s Power$</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1871_trader_april-1" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-1-a" mid="14" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>In any case, you’ll know what happens when you're done, right?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="7"><![CDATA[<html>$Merchant April$<BR>But shouldn't you be concerned it might have been the thing you were looking for? Of course, one has to be bold to produce good works...</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1871_trader_april-1-a" image="QS_Default.dds" itemindex="400699" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-1-b" mid="16" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>We’ve collected everything we need now.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="15"><![CDATA[<html>$Merchant April$<BR>Well, that's true too. If I worry about what’s to come, it's just a headache. Oh, come to think of it, here, take this.<BR>While you were looking for the <FONT color=#a82424>Sea Jewel</FONT>, I got the <FONT color=#a82424>Old Mechanism</FONT> all ready.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1871_trader_april-1-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-1-c" mid="18" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Isn’t that contrary to the store policy you mentioned earlier?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="17"><![CDATA[<html>$Merchant April$<BR>At April’s General Store, it's store policy that, if you need something, you can get as much as you want.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1871_trader_april-1-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-1-d" mid="20" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(It sounded something like that, but...)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="19"><![CDATA[<html>$Merchant April$<BR>That's the first policy, this is the second. Both policies are equally strictly followed.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1871_trader_april-1-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-1-e" mid="22" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>That's... Well, I don't think I can tell you in person. But it's not going to be a problem in Merca.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="21"><![CDATA[<html>$Merchant April$<BR>What I really wonder is what you're going to use them for.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
